node.text:
Ruhr Roam.
Creating lasting memories is simple, but not always easy. Getting up at 5am was tough, the weather looked miserable and the train we had planned to shoot got closed down. Cancelling our photo mission seemed like the obvious choice - but we didn’t. Instead @theolator came up with another dope location and @pangea called up the boys from @w.werft and asked if they’d be down for some paddling. The result: one of my favorite mornings of the year. Of course we suffered a bit, but we smiled a lot.
Anzeige | Thanks @adidasterrex for allowing us to change plans without having to change clothes. The Techrock jacket and its #goretex shell served us well that morning 👌🏻

node.text:
Lost in the Faroes.
I know it’s summer time and you probably wanna see green grass and sunshine, but I keep stumbling over shots from the wintry Faroe Islands. I guess I’ll always be drawn do those rugged islands far out in the Atlantic Ocean, no matter what season I’m in…
w/ @theolator

node.text:
Western Woods
That’s the literal translation of Westerwald, a forest range in the heart of Germany. It’s my girlfriend’s home region and every time we visit she shows me new pretty places. These trips aren’t about big hikes and lot’s of gear, all we bring is a camera and comfy clothes.
Anzeige // The comfy companion on my feet is the all new Solar Wave sneaker by @timberland_eu. It doesn’t just look good in nature, it’s also kind to nature! How exactly? The #greenstride sole is made of 75% renewable sugar cane, the #ReBOTL upper contains at least 50% recycled plastic and the footbed is 70% bio-based. Timberland is committed to create better products for a greener world and I’ll happily tag along. #timberland #timberland_eu

node.text:
Faroeminiscing.
It’s been 3 years since I took this shot. Somehow it feels even longer, yet I remember it as if it was yesterday. Memories as golden as the light in this photograph. ☀️
